While the bug has been fixed, the default parameter panel in the analysis view's
parameter editor no longer has a purpose.  That is to say, if you modify an
original default parameter in the analysis view, there is no effect on the
parameters that were originally set to default in the GCM editor.  If we are to
give the default parameter panel a purpose, then I propose that we add "default"
alongside "original" and "modified" to the drop down menus in the other
parameter editor panels.  When a user would choose default for a parameter, it
would be set to the original or modified default specified in the analysis
view's default parameter panel.

